10: That should've been the last of them.
14:
Nice work. I officially pronounce this 
zone cleared.
18:
Wait. Why've you been sticking to the 
rear?
22:
Nimbus. If you're unhappy with our 
formation, then I—
25:
Shut it. That's not what I'm talking 
about.
I want to know what you're scared of, 
Alk.
33:
You really the same guy I fought in 
the desert?
49: Why? It wasn't time for a shift yet...
56:
Yeah, you are... For the first time in a 
while.
66:
Why retreat? There's no one for you 
to hide behind.
74:
Come on. Who else fights like this?
I'm you. A shadow of you, anyways.
76:
I just want to talk. I want to ask how 
long you're going to stick with this 
senseless adventure.
82:
You don't have a great destiny to 
fulfill, like Light or Stella. You don't 
even have brute strength, like Nimbus.
84: So why are you trying so hard?
90:
Everyone else has a purpose. 
Motivation. Drive.
You're just a rowboat, going with the 
flow.
93:
No! I... I want my memories back! 
I want to find a way home!
96:
Don't lie to yourself.
You're scared. Scared of who you 
really are.
98:
What if you remember you're a 
normal kid from a normal home with 
the normal comforts? What would 
you be fighting for then?
106:
I didn't ask what THEY were fighting 
for. I asked about YOU!
112:
Why don't you quit while you're 
ahead? Leave before you get left be—
126:
You mess with my friends... you mess 
with me!
130:
I can't tell what you're thinking. You're 
a beast. You move by instinct. And 
you're so much stronger than me. To 
be honest—
134: Nimbus! Get out of the way!
141: Why are you so angry? Was I wrong?
144:
No... You're probably right. Chances 
are, I'm not special.
146:
But that doesn't mean I can't try. That 
doesn't mean I can't be part of 
something bigger and better than me!
And fine! I do think Nimbus is a grouch
and, frankly, kind of scary!
154:
No one decides what the truth is... But
me!
163:
One day, they're not going to need 
you anymore.
164:
They're going leave you behind... 
Throw you away.
Are you really okay with that?
168:
You're wrong. If we ever part ways, it 
won't be because they abandoned 
me... It'll be because I stopped 
following them.
171:
And that's fine, you know? Because, 
by then, at least I'll know... I did 
everything I could to contribute to 
something good.
181:
Hey. I'll admit I'm a grouch. But what 
part of me's scary?
187:
Well, too bad. I was born with these 
fangs!
190:
Yeah, I know... Sorry. I'll probably get 
used to them.
192:
Uh, Nimbus? The room's kind of 
starting to spin. Mind carrying me for 
a while?
198: Might help me get used to you faster.
201:
Fine. But if you complain about 
comfort or smell, I'm dropping you like 
a sack of hot potatoes.
210:
Shut up. Damn, it's like you're 
delivering your death monologue or—
Alk!
